---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import { SITE } from '../config';
---

<Base
  title="Affiliate Disclosure"
  description={`How ${SITE.name} makes money and how that affects our reviews. Full transparency on affiliate relationships and editorial independence.`}
>
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12 pb-20">

    <nav class="text-xs text-slate-400 mb-6 flex items-center gap-1.5">
      <a href="/" class="hover:text-brand-600">Home</a>
      <span>›</span>
      <span class="text-slate-600">Affiliate Disclosure</span>
    </nav>

    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-2">Affiliate Disclosure</h1>
    <p class="text-sm text-slate-500 mb-10">Last updated: {SITE.lastReviewed}</p>

    <div class="prose-custom">

      <h2>Does {SITE.name} earn money from the companies it reviews?</h2>
      <p>
        Yes, in some cases. {SITE.name} may earn a referral fee or commission when a reader
        clicks an outbound link to a company listed on this site and subsequently purchases a
        service or signs a contract. This is commonly called an affiliate or referral arrangement.
      </p>
      <p>
        Not all companies listed on this site have an affiliate arrangement with us.
        Companies that do are marked with a visible <strong>Sponsored</strong> label on their
        card and review page. Outbound links to those companies carry a <code>rel="sponsored"</code>
        attribute in the HTML, which is disclosed to search engines in line with Google's guidelines.
      </p>

      <h2>How does this affect our reviews and ratings?</h2>
      <p>
        Editorial ratings and review content are produced independently of any commercial
        arrangement. The presence or absence of an affiliate relationship does not determine
        which companies are included in our directory, what rating they receive, or what
        is written in their review.
      </p>
      <p>
        Specifically:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>We do not accept payment to influence editorial ratings.</li>
        <li>We do not accept payment to publish positive review content.</li>
        <li>Companies cannot purchase inclusion in the directory.</li>
        <li>A company with an affiliate arrangement is reviewed using the same criteria
            as a company with no commercial relationship.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>How can I tell which links are affiliate links?</h2>
      <p>
        On company cards and review pages, look for the <strong>Sponsored</strong> badge.
        Any "Visit site" or outbound link associated with a sponsored company is an affiliate link.
        Non-sponsored company links carry no commission.
      </p>

      <h2>Why does {SITE.name} use affiliate links?</h2>
      <p>
        Affiliate income allows us to invest time in researching, writing, and maintaining
        independent reviews without charging readers a subscription fee. We believe this
        model is preferable to paywalls, provided commercial relationships are fully disclosed
        and do not influence editorial content — which is our commitment on this site.
      </p>

      <h2>What should I do before hiring any company listed here?</h2>
      <p>
        All reviews on this site are based on publicly available information: company websites,
        published case studies, press releases, and industry sources. We verify facts where
        possible and use neutral language for claims we cannot confirm directly.
      </p>
      <p>
        Regardless of what any review says, you should:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Verify current services and pricing directly with the company.</li>
        <li>Request client references before committing to an engagement.</li>
        <li>Review contract terms, IP ownership clauses, and data handling practices independently.</li>
        <li>Conduct your own due diligence appropriate to the scale and sensitivity of your project.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Questions about this disclosure?</h2>
      <p>
        If you have questions about our affiliate relationships or editorial process,
        the <a href="/">homepage</a> links to all publicly available contact methods.
      </p>

    </div>
  </div>
</Base>
